# CLEAR Release Workflow

Use this rule when the user asks to cut or publish a release.

## Required flow

1. Follow `.github/skills/release.md`.
2. Publish release artifacts (`.sh`, `.sha256`, `.sha256.asc`).
3. After successful publish, update README "CLEAR in 60 Seconds" to the latest release tag.
4. README must include exact copy/paste download commands and verification commands.
5. Run `./clear/verify-ci.sh` before reporting completion.
